body:
@gunan You CAN run a linux docker container thought [docker for windows](https://docs.docker.com/docker-for-windows/#switch-between-windows-and-linux-containers), but it is based on vm and it didn't support gpu.

I have provided a 32 bit tensorflow built for windows, although it's not a helpful thing.

32-bit process can use only 2GB memory; a complex model would not load.
